description: In this final volume, Teito desperately seeks a way to drag both himself and Frau out of Verloren’s scythe for a final confrontation with the villainous death god. When the decisive moment comes, will Teito sacrifice himself to save the world he loves? Follow Teito on the last steps of his journey to prove love’s triumph over evil!
name: Vol. 17

description:
In the early 21st century, the majority of Earth's landmass is submerged due to rising sea levels. Enter the Fleet of Fog, a host of sentient alien battleships of unknown origin who easily decimate earth's naval forces. Humanity is now on the verge of extinction.

In the year 2039, the stalwart Captain Chihaya Gunzou and his intrepid crew on the Blue Steel fleet may be humanity's last chance to fight off the alien invaders. The Blue Steel fleet happens to contain a secret weapon that could turn the tide of war: a mysterious I-401 submarine that can transform into a girl.

Back Blurb

The Unlikeliest of Friends

The mansion where Professor Osakabe and Makie live is under attack, and nobody is happy about it: not the government, not the residents, and not even the attacking soldiers, who find themselves face to face with Haruna and learn firsthand that even without their battleships, the Fog's mental models are a force to be reckoned with!

Haruna's world has been turned upside down since the I-401 destroyed her and Kirishima's battleships. She's learned that Osakabe Makie is a Design Child, and a potentially valuable resource for the Fog, but Makie has also become her friend. And now Haruna is quickly learning the meaning of both "friendship" and "loss"---concepts she's never had to grapple with before.
name: Vol. 5

description: High school students Taehee and Yohan meet in a motorcycle accident. From then on their relationship slowly grows. But things get complicated because of Jinsuk, the teacher who's obsessed with Yohan.
name: Vol. 1

description:
The Mystery of Lavender Manor

A man is found beaten senseless in a parking lot, and the criminal he fingers is...George? Time for the Junior Detective League to spring into action and clear their friend's name!

Then a discovery in the school library reminds Conan of one of his first cases. Flash back to the young Jimmy and Rachel as they track down a sinister intruder in their elementary school after dark...an intruder who seems to have supernatural powers! Can two ordinary kids solve a code left by a master of mysteries?

Chapter Titles

  • File 1: The Sleuths' Grand Deduction
  • File 2: Hot-Blooded Detective
  • File 3: George Shoots
  • File 4: George and El
  • File 5: Mischievous Child
  • File 6: Under the Moon
  • File 7: Dawn
  • File 8: High Noon
  • File 9: Sunset
  • File 10: Eva's Secret (1)
  • File 11: Eva's Secret (2)
name: The Mystery of Lavender Manor

description: By accident, Eunyo burns down the house Inan inherited. They make a deal where Eunyo agrees to dress up like a man and work with Inan as a singing duo.
name: Vol. 2

description: Abandoned on the battlefield by the handsome Gayoon, Chaeun desperately fights off an endless bug onslaught only to be rescued by the mysterious renegade leader Moonhoo. At first, the man playfully flirts with Chaeun, but slowly the realization dawns that Moonhoo and his Core Hunter group have insidious ambitions on the dimensional portals.
name: Vol. 1

description: Only a pardon from the Water King himself can save Sooyi's father. The desperate Sooyi climbs the deadly mountain and reaches the Water King's palace, but the price for her father's pardon might just be her body and soul.
name: Vol. 4

description:
Izumi Sena is an average guy born into a family of famous celebrities. A college student and total otaku, he works hard every day with the goal of someday becoming a manga creator. But right now, he's somehow found himself stuck doing a commercial with popular actor Ryoma Ichijo. To make matters worse, Ryoma makes the situation even more awkward by professing his undying love.

Act 6 - 10, 10.5 & 10.8.
name: Volume 2

description:
My Neighbor Seki is a collection of short stories that revolve around two classmates who sit at the back of their high school homeroom. In each chapter Seki devises a new way to kill time in his school desk, to best avoid boredom. And along the way, he ends up distracting the girl who sits next to him Rumi; who's mind goes wild as Seki pushes the limits of his disobediance. Seki's humor is extremely thoughtful and mainly visually based. Author Morishige has compiled dozens of creative ways to kill time, but has brilliantly rendered those everyday ideas to curiously work within the restrictions of a high school classroom.

Contains 29th Period - 42nd Period & three Bonus stories.
name: A Quiet Storm

description: Meet Picolet Chardin II, master of the très terrifying La Belle France School of Martial Arts Dining. A style of martial arts based on eating doesn't seem like it would be hard to master…but if Ranma can't defeat Picolet in La Belle France, it'll be wedding bells! Then, the unfortunately named "Pantyhose Taro" makes trouble for Ranma and the others, but who's really the target—and cause—of all the vengeance?
name: Vol. 17 & 18

description: Fall turns to winter, and in the next world everyone is out looking for mushrooms. Gathering around the stew pot stirs the appetite and challenges Rinne to stay focused on his mission to exorcise ghosts! When Tamako’s Black Cat by contract Kuroboshi and his grandson, Kuroboshi the 3rd, arrive it looks like Rinne’s winter vacation is going to be all business!
name: Vol. 18

description: One day, a group of mysterious warriors arrive on the island and Sooho realizes that his vampire master is actually a king. And the fate of the world rests upon his blood.
name: Vol. 2

description: At Justice Tower, Tiger, Barnaby and Rock Bison confront Jake, but they’re no match for his unique powers and take a beating. Meanwhile, Origami Cyclone and Edward head to Jake’s secret hideout hoping to capture Kriem and stop the Mad Bears. With the data chip they recover, Saito discovers a way to stop the creepy toys, but the plan requires manpower the team doesn’t have. Fortunately, unlikely allies arrive just in time to offer assistance.
name: Vol. 7

description: Toru, the son of a yakuza boss, is sent into exile on a deserted island for his own protection during a gang feud. Fiery and impetuous, he isn't thrilled to be sidelined when he'd rather be in the fight, and is even less thrilled that Mutsumi, son of the gang's second in command, is going with him. The serious, studious Mutsumi is Toru's opposite in every way, and it doesn't take long before the sparks between them begin to fly!
name: The Case of Ritsu Onodera 2

description: Batman seeks out a former mentor, but Lex Luthor can’t be sure that trusting the newly-revealed Superman and Wonder Woman is any safer than believing in the promise of the Forever People.

description: As Superman recovers from Alpert’s attempt to give him the Forever People treatment, Wonder Woman tries to convince him that staying at the institute offers their best chance at discovering what’s really going on.
